wifi: mt76: mt7925: fix TX power reporting in AP mode

mt7925 computes phy->txpower_cur from hw->conf.power_level, which is
always 0 for chanctx-capable drivers in AP mode. mac80211 delivers
per-BSS TX power via BSS_CHANGED_TXPOWER instead, but mt7925 ignored
this event. This caused mt76_get_txpower() to report 0 dBm.

Add a txpower field to mt792x_phy to store the per-BSS TX power from
mac80211. Handle BSS_CHANGED_TXPOWER in mt7925_link_info_changed() to
update this field and recalculate power limits. Use the stored value
instead of hw->conf.power_level when computing phy->txpower_cur in
mt7925_mcu_set_rate_txpower().

This mirrors how mt7996 handles TX power via its own phy->txpower
field and BSS_CHANGED_TXPOWER handler.

Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>
Tested-by: Patryk Kowalczyk <patryk@kowalczyk.ws>

b5cf106cef0dceb66e01c7f0b54a9c6cef86c524
diff --git a/mt7925/main.c b/mt7925/main.c
index 825251f..844f8ff 100644
--- a/mt7925/main.c
+++ b/mt7925/main.c
@@ -1994,2 +1994,8 @@ static void mt7925_link_info_changed(struct ieee80211_hw *hw,
 
+	if (changed & BSS_CHANGED_TXPOWER &&
+	    info->txpower != phy->txpower) {
+		phy->txpower = info->txpower;
+		mt7925_mcu_set_rate_txpower(phy->mt76);
+	}
+
 	mt792x_mutex_release(dev);
diff --git a/mt7925/mcu.c b/mt7925/mcu.c
index 55c4975..360cc4d 100644
--- a/mt7925/mcu.c
+++ b/mt7925/mcu.c
@@ -3918,3 +3918,3 @@ int mt7925_mcu_set_rate_txpower(struct mt76_phy *phy)
 		tx_power = mt76_get_power_bound(phy,
-						mdev->hw->conf.power_level);
+						dev->phy.txpower);
 		tx_power = mt76_get_rate_power_limits(phy,
diff --git a/mt792x.h b/mt792x.h
index d456c57..d5607dc 100644
--- a/mt792x.h
+++ b/mt792x.h
@@ -169,2 +169,4 @@ struct mt792x_phy {
 
+	int txpower;
+
 	u32 rx_ampdu_ts;
